    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Swampscott
                                        Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed that on the 17th instant at 8.30 p.m., by Pennsylvania
                            Railroad, in special car No. 5841, a consignment of arms and ammunition,
                            comprising 450 boxes ammunition, 20 boxes of rifles marked <hi rend="italic">a</hi> in a diamond, has been sent to Charles Raymond,
                            esq., Southport, N. C. These arms, I am informed, are for the insurgents
                            in Cuba, and will be shipped probably to steamer <hi rend="italic">Commodore</hi>, which left New London, Conn., a few days ago. Will
                            return to Washington as soon as my health will permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dupuy de Lôme</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
